elpy (1.23.0-2) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Revert "Compress README.rst with gzip before installing" because
    README.rst is only 2.8k and dh_compress already does the right thing
    automatically; that is to say, README.rst is not "larger than 4k in
    size" and should not be compressed.
  * Add Debian-specific configuration to default to using Python 3.
  * Add patches that allow pip-related tests to pass with python3:
    - 0003-Allow-pip-related-tests-to-pass-with-python3-or-usr-.patch
    - 0004-Tighten-the-regex-used-in-Allow-pip-related-tests-to.patch
  * debian/control:
    - Drop python2 dependencies which are no longer needed
      for self-tests to pass.
    - Put ELPA dependencies section before Python ones (more alphabetical).

 -- Nicholas D Steeves <nsteeves@gmail.com>  Fri, 10 Aug 2018 19:19:16 -0400

